{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place dark chocolate into mixing bowl and grate <b>8 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add cocoa powder, full cream milk, cream, sugar, egg yolks and salt (optional) and cook <b>8 min\/90°C\/speed 2<b>. Then blend <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b> <strong>-<\/strong> <strong>7, increasing speed gradually<\/strong>. Pour mixture, up to 4 cm high, into shallow freezable containers (e.g. aluminium, silicone) or 3 - 4 ice cube trays and cover with plastic wrap. Allow mixture to cool completely before placing into freezer for at least 10 hours.","Place frozen mixture into refrigerator for 15 minutes, then cut into pieces (4 x 4 cm) with a long sharp knife. Place half the pieces into mixing bowl and crush <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>, then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b> with aid of spatula. Transfer ice cream into a bowl.","Place remaining frozen cream pieces into mixing bowl and crush <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>, then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b> with aid of spatula. Transfer into bowl with first batch and serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g dark chocolate (70% cocoa), cut into pieces (1 - 2 cm)","50 g cocoa powder","400 g full cream milk","200 g pouring (whipping) cream","150 g sugar","4 egg yolks","1 pinch salt              (optional)"]}],"id":"r68031","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-CCQb2rjXSlc\/XZanNkL5QFI\/AAAAAAAAg74\/tL6mAXvoHP85YQFdfEFQGlftN7TpvM7pgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6jjN2C3Bk84hjMXu.png","title":"Chocolate ice cream","publishedAt":"2014-09-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6 g","fat":"19 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"27 g","calories":"1291 kJ \/ 309 kcal"},"usefulItems":"plastic wrap, shallow freezable containers (e.g. aluminium, silicone), 3 - 4 ice cube trays, freezable serving dish, freezer, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["For a firm consistency, place the ice cream in a freezable serving dish and into the freezer for 15 minutes before serving.","D